CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 23, 1960, pg. 3 reads: "Seek Ward Posts - At Tuesday's rally, by the 13th Ward "Rebels" in Westinghouse High School auditorium, were the persons shown in this photo and in one next to this on the right, all of whom are supporting Atty. Linn Washington for the 13th Ward chairmanship. Above, left to right: John Conley, Elsie Neal, Isabella Yonkers, Wendall Allen, Rosina Quarles, Gerald Fox, Dorothy Elliott, Augustine Hopkins, Sallie Finch, Joseph Watts, Edward Meeks, Mary Jean Shipmon Brown, Sterling Perkins, Thelma Blye and William Booker."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: John Conley, Elsie Neal, Isabella Yonkers, Wendall Allen, Rosina Quarles, Gerald Fox, Dorothy Elliott, Augustine Hopkins, Sallie Finch, Joseph Watts, Edward Meeks, Mary Jean Shipmon Brown, Sterling Perkins, Thelma Blye, and William Booker, seated in semicircle for rally by the 13th Ward "Rebels," Westinghouse High School auditorium
